 Ngqeleni - A 27-year-old man has been arrested by Ngqeleni Detectives, who were following up on a case of business robbery at Mqwangqweni locality on Boxing Day, at about 04h00. "The suspect was found in possession of groceries, cosmetics and tobacco packs believed to have been stolen during the robbery and has been positively linked to the crime," said police spokesperson, Captain Dineo Koena. "More arrests and recoveries are expected as investigations are continuing." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  